Permutations with Square-Free Prefix Sums and OEIS Sequence
A395620
Abstract
We study permutations of {1,2,...,n}whose prefix sums avoid perfect squares. This com-
binatorial constraint defines the OEIS sequence A395620. We provide a formal framework,
a dynamic programming formulation for exact enumeration, complexity analysis, probabilistic
heuristics, and several generalizations. We also discuss structural properties and open problems
related to this class of restricted permutations.
1 Introduction
Let Sn denote the symmetric group on nelements. We consider permutations with a global additive
constraint: no prefix sum is allowed to be a perfect square.
Such problems belong to the general family of permutation pattern avoidance problems with
arithmetic constraints. Unlike classical pattern avoidance, the restriction here depends on cumula-
tive structure rather than local order.
This construction corresponds to OEIS sequence A395620.
