8 Open problems
We highlight several open directions:
• Does a(n) admit a closed form or recurrence?
• What is the precise asymptotic growth rate of a(n)?
• Is the sequence log-concave or unimodal in any transformed sense?
• Can one characterize forbidden-prefix structures combinatorially?
• Is there a bijection to known permutation-avoidance classes?
9 Conclusion
We introduced and studied permutations with square-free prefix sums, corresponding to OEIS
A395620. While exact enumeration is computationally expensive, the problem exhibits rich combi-
natorial structure and connects naturally to constrained path counting and additive combinatorics.
Further work includes asymptotic analysis and structural characterization of valid permutations.
